entries.femaleVariant: Look. Hey, look. See that?
Sons of bitches…
Jesus, they really are everywhere.
Gee, aren't you funny? Look around, look what they've done to this 'hood.
No, it's the part where I say I despise petty merc-thiefs who think they're hot shit rebels after settin' foot in the Afterlife.
Arasaka killed you, too, 'member.
Got yourself killed by 'em too. An' I'd just as soon not take advice from a digital corpse.
That what they teach folks in 'Saka these days? To shut down, cut power the moment truth looks 'em in the eye?
Know what? 'Fraid I don't got time for chit-chat.
You lack the cred, you lack the gusto – that's your problem.
entries.maleVariant: Lackin' the balls, that's your problem.

entries.femaleVariant: Got exactly no rep in this town and the chooms to match.
Whatever you gotta say – say it. Got somethin' eatin' at your code, that's clear.
Been tryin' to learn how you're wired this whole time. To know who I'm dealin' with.
Thought you were just unlucky at first. But I kept watchin' and finally realized what your problem is.
[Sit] Seem to know a lot about my past.
Sure seem to know a lot about my past.
Well, seen flashes of your past, just like you've seen flashes of mine.
Scared I'll lose myself, stop being me.
That pisses me off.
Pisses me off that our memories blend, don't have my own anymore. Chip's the worst thing to ever fuckin' happen to me.
Mean to say I haven't earned the top spot yet?
An arrogant asshole's no small problem, but it ain't my biggest. Dyin' is.
Death by becoming someone else... You didn't do anything to deserve that fate.
You're a dick, y'know.
And you're a cunt. Maybe we'll fit together after all?
Honestly, I'm scared of the day I'll start seeing your memories as my own.
Shit, if it's a two-way street, I'll somehow have to live with the fact that I let DeShawn best me, fuck me over.
Listen, will I notice the change? Or, is it one of those things where I'll wonder why I ever feared it?
entries.maleVariant: So listen, will-- will I notice a change? Or, is it one of those things where I'll wonder why I ever feared it?

entries.femaleVariant: Worst thing you can do to a human – rip their identity out of 'em. That's all I know.
What do you want from me, really?
What's it like, bein' in someone else's head?
[End convo] Don't need your sympathy.
Can you just tell me what you want? What you really want?
Help me settle my score against Arasaka. That's it.
My memories – what do they… feel like?
Not followin' ya.
Aside from what you see and hear, I mean. You processs or experience any feelings?
Anger, regret, bitterness, fear. Though honestly, can't tell if they're yours or mine.
How you find life under my skin?
Well, most things're either too big or too small. Not to mention the clusterfuck that're your hormones.
Don't need your sympathy.
You fuckin' gonk! I'm tryin' to help you!
You afraid of death?
I'm afraid of wasted opportunities.
Like Arasaka Tower?
Came through it, as you can see. And I ain't done with them yet.
Incapable of sitting still, letting anything go, aren't you.
You got no idea what you want.
Not having control – you can't stand it. Seeing some things're outta your hands…
Don't be ridiculous, V.
Let's cut this juvenile bullshit.
I'm just tryin' to help you!
It's a TV. Didn't have those fifty years ago?
Like jokes, think it's funny? Look around – used to be crops in all directions... till the corps started fucking the farmers silly.
And you really are paranoid.
You don't see it? Way corps are strippin' our world and lives naked, piece by piece? Can't turn a blind eye to that.
This the part where you divulge your master plan to annihilate Arasaka?
Piss off.
What the fuck you want – just tell me.
Says the most inept terrorist in human history. Need I remind you how you let Arasaka crush your soul and put you here?
Hah! I brought war to their doorstep, kid. Your grand plan? To steal their fuckin' car.
A nomad could never understand what it means to fight for this city, die for it.
Ain't the only one to get flatlined by 'Saka. 'Cept I didn't let them scoop out my mind, digilock it in a trinket.
entries.maleVariant: Ain't the only one to get flatlined by 'Saka. 'Cept I didn't let 'em scoop out my mind, digilock it in a trinket.

entries.femaleVariant: Still got better prospects than a carbon-copy ghost of a washed-up rockerboy locked in a trinket.
Your last "prospect" was to net some eddies on a stolen biochip. Remember how that went?
Always been a corpocog, a replaceable part.
You were a kid from the Badlands, family was your crutch and cushion.
You're a dirtgirl from Heywood who found the guts to walk a few extra blocks from home.
entries.maleVariant: You're a dirtboy from Heywood who found the guts to walk a few extra blocks from home.

entries.femaleVariant: Once 'Saka booted you out, stripped you of perks, best you could hope for was to be a scav exterminator.
But in NC you're nobody, best you can do is steal from scavs – the merc janitors.
But turned out the best you can do is chase scavs for ennies.
And the lag between sight and touch – infuriating. When you take a bite of pizza, takes ages before I know you fuckin' burned the roof of your mouth.
Plus, used to be five minutes wouldn't pass 'fore I had a fresh cig in my hand, now I'm itchin' for nicotine.
Gettin' used to it, I guess, but its' no fuckin' picnic.
An enemy – you need to have one at all times.
Know what? Seems to me you need to have a nemesis, at all times.
Ideally a crazy powerful one to feed your ego… and they've gotta be pratically unbeatable – to justify a suicide run.
Heh. You're funny.
Actually, that's what I am, that kind of nemesis – I'll decide your fate, fuck all you can do.
entries.maleVariant: Actually, that's what I am, that kind of nemesis – I'll decide your fate, and there's fuck all you can do.

entries.femaleVariant: Whup – another speech about demolishing Arasaka incoming.
Not up for this discussion.
Why're we talkin' about this?
Where you headin' off to?!
The moment when I turn into you – will I notice it?
How's life in my body?
You afraid of death?
You watchin' a story on the Arasakas or narrating porn…?
Might think you took on Arasaka, but you're just a bug they scraped off the sole of their boot and tossed in the trash.
Why can't you just leave me alone?
As I see it, you don't know what you really want, so you concocted a bogeyman to fight – Arasaka.
Got a clear goal. Like I do.
Don't think I care. What does interest me is why you're a clingy creep.
Your goal's to bury Arasaka, demolish it. Mine's to stay above ground. Seem pretty clearly defined, both.
Whole world used to revolve around Silverhand. Now, no one gives a shit.
Heh. You're funny.
Got a new life, you did, but you got exactly no idea what to do with it.
Honestly, don't differ a bit from those poor bastards handcuffed to the feeders in their megablock pads.
OK, I'll tell ya why I wanna destroy Arasaka, but I'll only tell ya once. Wanna hear it?
Yeah.
[End convo] Hmm... No.
All right.
Uh, no – not interested.
I saw corps strip farmers of water... and eventually of land.
Don't need your help, either!
Back to your cell, Johnny. Time's up.
I neither want nor do I need your help.
entries.maleVariant: Well, I neither want nor do I need your help.

entries.femaleVariant: Just go – had enough of you…
Gotta go. Hang in there, bud.
Actually align pretty nicely, too. You need Mikoshi to save your life – that done, I can burn it to the ground.
Ah, there it is – the crusade. Get to Mikoshi, smash the System.
entries.maleVariant: And there it is – the crusade. Get to Mikoshi, smash the System.

entries.femaleVariant: Saw them transform Night City into a machine fueled by people's crushed spirits, broken dreams and emptied pockets.
Corps've long controlled our lives, taken lots... and now they're after our souls!
Damn straight.
Don't exaggerate.
Might be right, can't really argue with you there.
C'mon, don't exaggerate.
V, I've declared war not 'cause capitalism's a thorn in my side or outta nostalgia for an America gone by.
This war's a people's war against a system that's spiralled outta our control. It's a war against the fuckin' forces of entropy, understand?!
Johnny, take a sec, we gotta--
You still don't see it. But you will one day.
Do whatever it takes to stop 'em, defeat 'em, gut 'em. If I gotta kill, I'll kill. If I need your body, I'll fuckin' take it!
Johnny...
I think we can work together, V.
But your plans make no sense. Destroy Arasaka? I don't even know what that means.
entries.maleVariant: But your plan makes no sense. Destroy Arasaka? I-- I don't even know what that means.

entries.femaleVariant: All in good time.
Fuck those cunts…
See that? Fuck me, just look at that.
Just take a look! Get what I mean now?
Turnin' your back on the problem, again?!
Gonna leave me, drop me, forget me like you did Jackie Welles?!
You fuckin' pitiful petty klepper!
Let's blow, get outta here…
Johnny...
Fuckin' leprous Arasaka again?
[Stand]
[End convo] Not in the mood for your cheap psychoanalysis.
You're the worst kind of asshole.
Least I'm still allive.
You've become no one – makes you anxious as fuck.
[End convo] Had enough of this spat.
[Stand]
[Stand]
[Stand]
Though not ideal, I'm a nemesis to you, too.
[End convo] OK, end of topic.
Got no idea who you are, what you're supposed to do.
[End convo] OK, done enough tongue flapping.
Man, do you go around in circles…
[End convo] Heard enough. I'm tired.
Paranoid – that's what you are.
It's a fucking video feed. Chill.
[End convo] Toodles…
